On Thu, 3 Jul 2003, Seann Stafford wrote:

> I have never much liked
> mounting my front plate to my front bumper, because the plate tends
> to hang lower than the bumper and occassionally will scrape when
> pulling into a steep driveway from a level street.  Kinda hard on
> the license plate.

For my early bay, the solution was to flip the license plate bracket over
so it points upward, then mount the plate by its lower holes.  Keeps the
plate above the bumper and doesn't look all that bad.

George Lyle
